If Everybody Loved the Same as You
comments: Contender to represent the UK at the 1977 Eurovision Song Contest but eventually placed 6th from 12 entries at the 'A Song for Europe' national selection show held on March 9th at the New London Theatre hosted by Terry Wogan . Due to a strike the contest was never shown on television, but was broadcast on the radio. The winning song was Rock Bottom by Lynsey De Paul and Mike Moran chosen by the votes of 14 regional juries.

The Eyes of Texas Are upon You
comments: Performed by a vocal quartet consisting of students (Jim Cannon, Jim Kivlehen, Ralph Porter and Bill Smith) accompanied by the lyricist, John Sinclair, on banjo. It was done as a joke on University of Texas president William Prather who was known to admonish students with the phrase, "the eyes of Texas are upon you."
